Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 2 YEARS, with credit for 0 (zero) days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 1 YEAR; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 1 YEAR.  The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Earned Release Program.
The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 3 YEARS with the following conditions:  

1) Mental Health evaluation, treatment as recommended.
2) Participate and complete OARS Program;
3) Cooperate with agent;
4) Pay supervision fees; 
5) Continue to see prescribing doctor, take medications in the manner as prescribed.
6) Provide a DNA sample;
7) Court waived all non-mandatory costs, fees, surcharges (including DNA surcharge) and assessments due to defendant's financial instability. 
     Any mandatory costs are due by March 13, 2017 or entry of a civil judgment. March 27, 2015 at 1:30 p.m. projected guilty plea vacated.

